<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4078] Number.step incorrectly believes there is an infinite loop</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4078</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;recently i noticed that an exception is thrown with something like&lt;br/&gt;
0.step 0, 10, {}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i checked the dgm (version 1.7.0 i think) and found that self and to equality is never considered as a possibility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i believe it should just do nothing like, say&lt;br/&gt;
(0..&amp;lt;0).step 10, {}&lt;br/&gt;
or&lt;br/&gt;
for (int i=0; i&amp;lt;0; i++) {}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
